    'Historical Context of Housing Affordability',
    'The history of housing affordability in the United States is deeply intertwined with economic shifts, societal transformations, and government policies. As urbanization accelerated, housing accessibility became a central policy concern, but many initiatives reflected the biases and limitations of their time.',
    'The federal government has repeatedly intervened in housing markets to address affordability, often with mixed results. Programs such as the National Housing Act of 1934 and subsequent legislation aimed to increase homeownership and rental availability but sometimes perpetuated systemic inequalities.',
